Course Name: Behind the Scenes of a Freshman at UIUC
Description: An insider's perspective on navigating the exciting journey of freshman year at the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign (UIUC)! Throughout this semester-long exploration, you will delve into various aspects of campus life, gaining invaluable insights into dorm food, dorm halls, classes, clubs, student life, and fun activities to do on campus.

Course Name: WCS: Developing a Problem Solving Mindset in CS
Description: Learn what it’s like to problem solve and think critically about challenging issues as a computer scientist and engineer! Join us for an interactive session where you will learn the thought process behind iterative programming and developing, debugging, and thorough testing while following along and completing a “machine project” of your own!

Course Name: RPG Game Development using Javascript with Codédex
Description: Build an RPG Game from top-to-bottom using Javascript Libraries! Learn about Game Design, Art, Music, and Production for a simple RPG game, and how you can use Codédex to learn Javascript and level up your coding knowledge!

An overview of how computer science is being used in media today! You'll learn about the different applications of computer science in media, such as audio, images, and video. Later,  you'll experiment with different audio and image algorithms.

Course Name: Introduction to Graph Theory: Graph Theory in the Real World
Description: Unlock the power of graph theory through learning essential graph algortihms and their real-life applications to enhance your problem solving skills

Course Name: Vim: CLI editing like a pro
Description: Become an effective programmer by learning command line editing tools!
Learn the various aspects of computer security by hacking through a fun, interactive narrative!
Teach a program how to intelligently play borad games such as chess, checkers, or scrabble through programming!

Course Name: Inside the Mind of a Hacker
Description: Launch into cybersecurity with a beginner-friendly introduction to the adversarial mindset to learn how to think like a hacker.
Learn how a 2-bit binary adder circuit works! In this class,  you'll be able to wire up your own circuit to add numbers!
Get an crash-course in creating, personalizing, and sharing your own website to showcase yourself!
Just a little bit of code can do a lot! Use Python to customize Wordle to what you want it to be!
Learn how to use Arduino in a bunch of different ways through computer science concepts, with a finale of a free-for-all light show!

Course Name: What is AI? Answers to the Big Questions!
Description: AI is more vast and applicable than you thought...Learn about what AI is, how it works, and its applications!
Get a high-level intro to Quantum Computing! How is it different from Classical Computing? What are its applications?

Course Name: Circuits to Code: A Primer on Computer Architecture
Description: A fly-by overview of the basics of computer architecture. You'll learn what computer architecture is and what you can expect from a computer engineering degree at UIUC. Work your way through logic gates and binary to understand the basics of an 8-bit computer.

The ability to recognize and capitalize on opportunities is incredibly important and this course aims to help you do so within the school setting and explore specific opportunities at U of I. We are here to empower you and help you identify opportunities and establish meaningful connections!

Course Name: WCS: How to be a Woman in CS
Description: What is it like being a woman in computer science and engineering? Join us for an interactive session where we’ll show you how to build a support system and community, increase your own confidence, deal with failure, as well as seek out career and mentorship opportunities. This will be followed by personal stories of women in CS at UIUC along with an open Q&A Panel!
This class will focus on some real problems you face and guide you on how you can use data structures in software to solve them!

Course Name: Automate the Boring Stuff with Python!
Description: In this class, you'll learn how to use Python to write programs that take minutes to do things that would take hours to do by hand - no prior programming experience required! Once you've mastered the basics of programming, you'll create Python programs that effortlessly perform useful and impressive feats of automation to
Take a deep dive into how recruitment season for internships and careers works and an overview of Engineering RSOs on campus!
Start your programming journey with Python! Learn about Jupyter Notebooks, solve open-ended problems, and get a general intro to Python.

Course Name: Circles and Lines: Introduction to Graph Theory with Real-Life Applications
Description: Dive into graph theory! Get an overview of a vast number of topics in graph theory (connectivity, coloring, path-finding, etc), and applications to other fields (linguistics, neuroscience, sociology, etc).
Learn about the basics of robotics through both physical examples as well as the theory behind them!
How to use the Spotify API and React to build a simpler version of Spotify Wrapped! You'll get the chance to play around with customizing your own websites and writing your first API calls!
Get a crash course into the theory of Functional Programming through demos, interactive exercises, and the lambda calculus behind it!
Learn the basics of computer graphics through Rasters, Rasterization, and WebGL!
Explore the concepts of recursion and induction by tackling problems and designing algorithms using these approaches.

Course Name: CybersecYOUrity: A Guide to Navigating Your Digital World through Cybersecurity Adventures and Pop Culture
Description: Learn why cybersecurity is important and how it affects YOU. Understand the realities of how cybersecurity works in the real world!

Course Name: Software to Silicon: How Your Code Actually Works
Description: Behind every program are layers and layers of complicated systems! This course will let you see what goes under the hood of your computer program.

Join us for a fun, interactive session on the basics of cryptography and cyphers! We will present a tutorial on how to get started with encryption through Python followed by an interactive workshop where you will learn more about the algorithms that go behind cyphers in computer science and engineering!

Course Name: How to get a SWE Internship
Description: A beginner's guide to getting a SWE internship, including interview prep, networking, resume format, applying online, and deciding where to apply. This course comes with a light presentation, a fun activity, and an open-ended conversation with any questions you have.
Explore algorithms in computer science!
Learn the intracacies of Binary Search, and the multitucde of problem-solving applications it can have, especially in coding interviews!
Explore how AI plays a role in our lives while playing around with some student AI projects!
How to make the most out of the resources offered in CS at UIUC! Tips and tricks for on-campus tutoring, office hours, and website-based learning.

Course Name: Intro to Machine Learning with Kaggle Titantic Dataset
Description: Learn the basics of machine learning using Python and how to use Kaggle datasets to your advantage
Get an intro to the JavaScript Language in the context of p5.js and learn how to creatively make your own graphics with it!

Course Name: Taste the Flavors of Computer Science
Description: Find the different pathways to be pursued in computer science such as SWE, Product Management, Quantitative Trading, and more, learning through interactive examples!
A hands-on tutorial on how to use the Spotify API! In this class, you'll write a Python program that mimics your Spotify Wrapped.

A workshop on creating your personal website! By combining interpersonal and technical skills,  this workshop will teach you personal branding and learning from your peers while building your own website.
